==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weakling
<hw>Weak"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Weak</ets> +
<ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <def>A weak or feeble creature.</def>
<au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧All looking on him as a <xex>weakling</xex>, which
would post to the grave.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Fuller.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We may not be <qex>weaklings</qex> because we have a strong
enemy.</q> <rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weakling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Weakling
<hw>Weak"ling</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Weak; feeble.</def> <rj><au>Sir
T. North.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

